headline.main: DOZEN AXIS PLANES WRECKED AT TUNIS; One American Machine Lands With Bomb Doors Jammed

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN NORTH AFRICA, Dec. 2 (AP) -- Pilots of American medium bombers that, with an escort of P-38 fighters, blasted the Tunis airdrome again today, reported at least twelve Axis bombers and transports destroyed on the ground.
abstract: Awards DSO and DSC to Capt Peters
